      "writtenOn": "2020-08-18T18:50:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is fine but none of the other validation logic is written this way. I\u0027m not sure anything is really gained by doing this. Why not call validateUpdateBuildStatus and validateTags directly from validateUpdate and avoid the indirection? In the case of validateTags you have extra indirection, because you can\u0027t call it directly since you don\u0027t know what type of argument you need to pass, you had to create validateUpdateBuildTags which does nothing except call validateTags with the correct arguments. And you had to define noop which is unnecessarily called on every one of these fields.",
      "revId": "0ba9837dfc10fdac8b650436b118e978ffa6184c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1a7d3d43_cbed4efe",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/rpc/update_build.go",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 41,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-18T20:00:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ack. I don\u0027t have a strong opinion on this, and can make the change as you suggested. However, here are the reasons of this change.\n\n-------------------------------------------------\nAFAIK, UpdateBuild() is the only function validating a request with acceptable field masks.\nThat\u0027s probably the reason why none of others are written this way. This is mainly for a readability purpose. In the existing code, including the python implementation, it doesn\u0027t seem super clear how each of the updatable field paths are connected with the validation. It becomes more clear if they are defined and associated together in a single map.\n\nI believe that golang compiler would optimize out noop() as it\u0027s too obvious; it unconditionally returns nil without any side-effect",
      "parentUuid": "56ac1032_97e31ae8",
      "revId": "0ba9837dfc10fdac8b650436b118e978ffa6184c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5fc4a497_3b574d96",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/rpc/update_build.go",
